(155, 1, '2014-03-07 12:05:14', '2014-03-07 12:05:14', 'I don''t intend  to give to much advices for this subject but I recomand the book "The power of full engagement" by Tony Swarts to all those that aren''t very luky to have a proper environment to define themselves and to archive their goals. The main ideea of this book is to continuously exercise, improve and work on the four levels of your person : the mental, intellectual, spiritual and physic. That because the problem of time management reduces at the problem of energy management.\r\n\r\nFor that to be accomplish you have to live targeting the  healt and wellness of yourself and those around you. So, there are some habits that you should have in your life. I can sum up those there :\r\n\r\n-you start the day at 6 a.m and you end the day at 10 p.m\r\n\r\n- drink plenty  of pure water during the day\r\n\r\n- eat small meals of a big variety of  fresh and natural aliments, but eat those dissociated (only after 2-3 hours of eating carbohidrets you can eat proteins); only after the food is digested you can drink water or a fresh from fruits; you can eat vegetables at each meal, but I bealive the salad of vegetables is for the  6 or 7 p.m meal.\r\n\r\n-you do only those activities that fill you with joy or help you in the process of archiving your goals.\r\n\r\n-you do physic exercises for your body ( gimmnastyc is the best, don''t struggle to much)\r\n\r\n-you learn each day and you prepare yourself in the field you want to excell\r\n\r\n- you write down your thoughts and keep track of projects, activities you make and plans you implement, easch time you have an ideea you should write it down, when you''ll have the necessary time to implement it, if it''s really good you''ll accomplish something great.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Keep the balance', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'keep-the-balance', '', '', '2014-03-07 12:05:14', '2014-03-07 12:05:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost/oltsoft.ro/?p=155', 0, 'post', '', 0),
